items.title: Thrust Into the Line of Fire, Iranians Worry About What Comes Next
items.description: A 12-day war in June upended the shadow war rivalry between Israel and Iran. Some Iranians want to strike back, others want to move on.

items.title: American Who Posed as Irish Heiress Is Found Guilty of Theft and Fraud
items.description: Marianne Smyth was convicted in Northern Ireland, and could face up to 10 years in prison.

items.title: What to Know About a Rapid U.S. Military Buildup in the Caribbean
items.description: The United States has deployed eight warships, several surveillance planes and one attack submarine to the region as tensions with Venezuela grow.

items.title: Large Shark Kills Surfer Near Sydney, Police Say
items.description: The authorities in Australia closed beaches in the northern Sydney suburbs after the attack.

items.title: With ‘Ghost Bat’ Drone, Australia Gears Up for New Arms Race
items.description: A new class of aircraft developed with Boeing, it will be the first military plane designed and manufactured in the country in half a century.
